{"title":"Colnago Unveils its Vision of Gravel Racing with the Italian Crafted C68 Gravel","link":"https://bikerumor.com/colnago-made-in-italy-c68-gravel-race-bike/","date":1706781600000,"content":"<p><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Grave Full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></p>\n<p><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shots-fired-boonen-bashes-colnago-it-punches-back/\">Colnago</a> knows a thing or two about drop-bar off-road bikes, even though most think of them as a road-only brand….thanks<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/pogacar-colnago-collection/\"> Pogačar.</a></p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"1764\" height=\"1176\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Colnago_new-Prestige_disc-brake-carbon-cyclocross-race-bike_photo-by-Wout-Van-Aert_Crelan_World-Champion-edition.jpg\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Colnago_new-Prestige_disc-brake-carbon-cyclocross-race-bike_photo-by-Wout-Van-Aert_Crelan_World-Champion-edition.jpg 1764w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Colnago_new-Prestige_disc-brake-carbon-cyclocross-race-bike_photo-by-Wout-Van-Aert_Crelan_World-Champion-edition-120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Colnago_new-Prestige_disc-brake-carbon-cyclocross-race-bike_photo-by-Wout-Van-Aert_Crelan_World-Champion-edition-297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Colnago_new-Prestige_disc-brake-carbon-cyclocross-race-bike_photo-by-Wout-Van-Aert_Crelan_World-Champion-edition-768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/09/Colnago_new-Prestige_disc-brake-carbon-cyclocross-race-bike_photo-by-Wout-Van-Aert_Crelan_World-Champion-edition-600x400.jpg 600w\" /><figcaption>Wout Van Aerts World Champion Edition Colnago Prestige (Photo: Cory Benson)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Let’s not forget that legends like Sven Nys and Niels Albert rode the Colnago Prestige — the same with a very young Wout Van Aert. <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/eb16-colnago-redesigns-prestige-disc-cyclocross-world-champion-plus-new-alloy-a1r-bikes-road-cx/\">The Prestige</a> would eventually fade out of the Colnago line. The World Cup and World Title winning machine was replaced with the gravel/cyclocross-focused<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/colnago-g3x-gravel-bike/\"> Colnago G-3X</a>. </p>\n\n\n\n<p>The G-3X is more of a gravel bike than a pure ‘cross-machine, but it does have that iconic Colnago kick and more tire clearance than the Prestige ever had.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-rear--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV rear\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-rear--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-rear--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-rear--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-rear--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-rear--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-rear--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-logo--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV logo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-logo--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-logo--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-logo--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-logo--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-logo--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-logo--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-cap-close-up--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV top cap close up\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-cap-close-up--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-cap-close-up--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-cap-close-up--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-cap-close-up--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-cap-close-up--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-cap-close-up--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Its all about the small touches. (Photo: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>In recent years, though, Colnago has put effort into re-thinking their business’s gravel side. Adding to it, they have created something pure Colnago. A performance-focused gravel bike. One that looks at home on the white roads of Tuscany or on twisty American single track (more on that later). Plus, it’s handmade in Italy.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-call-out--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV call out\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-call-out--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-call-out--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-call-out--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-call-out--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-call-out--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-call-out--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-call-out--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>The only ‘C68’ call out on the new Colnago C68 Gravel (Photo: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>What is the Colnago C Series</h2>\n\n\n\n<p>The C series is a moniker for the top tier of <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/pro-bike-nathan-haas-gets-retro-italian-airbrush-style-in-kansas-custom-colnago-g3-x-for-unbound/\">Colnago bikes</a>; the more attainable version for most is the ‘V’ series. The C68 bikes are handmade in Italy and aim to balance beauty and performance. The Colnago C68 Series of bikes boasts a Road, All-Road, Titanium Custom, and now a Gravel bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-tops--scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Grave tops\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-tops--scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-tops--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-tops--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-tops--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-tops--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-tops--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-tops--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-tops--720x480.jpg 720w\" /><figcaption>(Photo credit: Colnago)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Colnago describes the C Series as: “C for Carbon, Colnago, Cambiago (where the bikes are made), and<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/gorgeous-motoki-yoshio-x-colnago-matte-c68-heads-to-sothebys/\"> Class</a>. The 68 represents how far Colnago has come since its founding in 1954.”</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Ride--scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel Ride\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Ride--scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Ride--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Ride--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Ride--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Ride--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Ride--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Ride--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Ride--720x480.jpg 720w\" /><figcaption>(Photo credit: Colnago)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Colnago C68 Gravel Frame Details</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>There’s much to unpack here, so let’s start with the frame creation. First, the Colnago C68 is 100% hand-made from high-modulus carbon fiber. Some parts are lugged, making it also a modular frame.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV side view\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>(Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-joint--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV joint\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-joint--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-joint--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-joint--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-joint--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-joint--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-joint--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV frame assembly\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>What does Colnago mean by <em>‘modular’? </em></h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The C68 Gravel is comprised of six separate carbon pieces. The engineers designed the headtube/downtube and top tube junction to be maneuverable when building the frame. The tubes are lugged and modular, as the builder can move them slightly, augmenting the stack slightly, the same as the headtube height. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-together--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV frame assembly together\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-together--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-together--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-together--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-together--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-together--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-together--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Setup high with a taller headtube (Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-top-cap--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV frame assembly top cap\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-top-cap--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-top-cap--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-top-cap--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-top-cap--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-top-cap--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-top-cap--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Closeup of a finished carbon set</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-detail-top-cap--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV frame assembly detail top cap\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-detail-top-cap--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-detail-top-cap--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-detail-top-cap--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-detail-top-cap--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-detail-top-cap--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-detail-top-cap--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>This method is only used on the C series frames, though Colnago has used lugged carbon construction since the 1980s. The lugged tubes give the C68 Gravel a unique look, and the matte green pearl paint (similar to the Aston Martin) accentuates the curves.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-down-tube-and-water-bottle-detail--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV frame assembly down tube and water bottle detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-down-tube-and-water-bottle-detail--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-down-tube-and-water-bottle-detail--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-down-tube-and-water-bottle-detail--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-down-tube-and-water-bottle-detail--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-down-tube-and-water-bottle-detail--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-down-tube-and-water-bottle-detail--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>(Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottle-mounts--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV bottle mounts\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottle-mounts--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottle-mounts--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottle-mounts--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottle-mounts--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottle-mounts--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottle-mounts--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Yes to Top Tube Bag But No Third Bottle </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>As for modern gravel bits, the C68 has a top tube bag mount and can fit two large bottles (think 38oz) in the frame. There is no third bottle mount under the frame, so if you’re planning a super long, unsupported ride, you’ll need to plan accordingly. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-tube-detail--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV frame assembly tube detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-tube-detail--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-tube-detail--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-tube-detail--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-tube-detail--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-tube-detail--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-tube-detail--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>The edges of the carbon tubes are slightly tapered (Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-inside-tube-detail--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV frame assembly inside tube detail\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-inside-tube-detail--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-inside-tube-detail--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-inside-tube-detail--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-inside-tube-detail--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-inside-tube-detail--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-frame-assembly-inside-tube-detail--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-clearance--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV clearance\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-clearance--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-clearance--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-clearance--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-clearance--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-clearance--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-clearance--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The tube shaping in the C68 Gravel is designed for power transfer, minimizing road chatter, and handling a flying rock to the down tube without cracking. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV seatpost\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>The cover keeps the gravel out of your fittings and looks pretty cool. </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-binder--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV seatpost binder\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-binder--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-binder--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-binder--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-binder--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-binder--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-binder--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>The new tightening mechanism firmly holds the post in place without worry of slipping. (Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame uses a D-shaped seatpost similar to the one on the G-3X but with an updated tightening mechanism. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-made-in-italy--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV made in italy\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-made-in-italy--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-made-in-italy--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-made-in-italy--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-made-in-italy--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-made-in-italy--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-made-in-italy--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-made-in-italy--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The bottom bracket is a T47, the same as the C68 All Road.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-crank-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV crank\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-crank-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-crank-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-crank-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-crank-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-crank-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-crank-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>3D printed front derailleur covers are stock on the C68 Gravel (Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame is optimized for a fully electronic groupset but can run a mechanical 1X like the new<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/shimano-grx-12-speed-mechanical/\"> Shimano GRX 12-speed</a>. The placeholder for a front derailleur is a neat 3D-printed cover, which takes nothing away in performance but adds cool points. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-3d-printed-chain-guard--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV 3d printed chain guard\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-3d-printed-chain-guard--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-3d-printed-chain-guard--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-3d-printed-chain-guard--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-3d-printed-chain-guard--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-3d-printed-chain-guard--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-3d-printed-chain-guard--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-3d-printed-chain-guard--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Same with the chain guard (Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The chain guard is also 3D-printed and pictures the mountains of Italy.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-bar--scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel bar\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-bar--scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-bar--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-bar--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-bar--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-bar--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-bar--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-bar--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-bar--720x480.jpg 720w\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Colnago Gravel Geometry</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Though the C68 shares some features of the Prestige, All Road, and G-3X, it has a unique geometry. It has a shorter reach and higher stack than the C68 Road. The updated reach-stack ratio allows for a shorter stem, giving the bike a lively feel on the trails and lots of control over the front end. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"1240\" height=\"746\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Geo-.png\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel Geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Geo-.png 1240w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Geo--297x179.png 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Geo--800x481.png 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Geo--120x72.png 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-Geo--768x462.png 768w\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>C68 Gravel will be <strong>available in 5 sizes</strong>, all in sloping configuration: 450 (52cm), 480 (54cm), 510 (58cm), 540 (60cm), and 570 (63cm)</p>\n\n\n\n<p>Colnago feels this setup offers better handling for challenging gravel or trail features without sacrificing an aggressive setup. I agree after spending some hours on the bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-garmin-mount-800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV garmin mount\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-garmin-mount-800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-garmin-mount-297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-garmin-mount-120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-garmin-mount-768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-garmin-mount-1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-garmin-mount-2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>(Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-intigrated-cables--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV intigrated cables\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-intigrated-cables--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-intigrated-cables--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-intigrated-cables--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-intigrated-cables--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-intigrated-cables--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-intigrated-cables--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-options--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV bar options\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-options--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-options--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-options--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-options--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-options--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-options--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>All the bar offerings </figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Colnago CC.01 wide bar/stem combo riffs off the new C68 gravel geometery. The new Wide version of the CC.01 is specifically designed for gravel. The Colnago CC.01 Wide has more flare than the road version of the Colnago CC.01. The reach is 72.50 mm and a drop of 120mm with a stem angle of 82 degrees. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV bar\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>(Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"533\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-cation-shot--800x533.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Grave cation shot\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-cation-shot--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-cation-shot--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-cation-shot--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-cation-shot--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-cation-shot--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-cation-shot--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-cation-shot--720x480.jpg 720w\" /><figcaption>(Photo: Colnago)</figcaption></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Colnago CC.01 Wide is available in five different stem combinations with the same 40 hood and 46 wide at the drop: 80mm – 40/46, 90mm – 40/46, 100mm – 40/46, 110mm – 40/46, and 120mm – 40/46. The C68 Gravel complete bike arrives with the Colnago CC.01 Wide cockpit but is compatible with a traditional bar/stem combination.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottom-bracket--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV bottom bracket\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottom-bracket--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottom-bracket--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottom-bracket--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottom-bracket--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottom-bracket--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottom-bracket--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bottom-bracket--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>The tube shapes are sharper at the edge, closer to the look of the Colnago C68 road machine.(Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>How about tire clearance?</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>When I asked about tire clearance, the Colnago team calmly stated, <em>“Up to 42mm but it performs best with the 40s”. </em>Why not 50mm or something more extensive like the trend? The team told me,<em> “This isn’t that kind of gravel bike.”</em> The C68 is a fast bike designed around a more aggressive riding style, leaning more toward the gravel-road/racing side.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-tire-clearance--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV top tire clearance\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-tire-clearance--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-tire-clearance--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-tire-clearance--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-tire-clearance--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-tire-clearance--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-top-tire-clearance--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Pictured is a 40mm Pirelli Cinturato Gravel on Enve SES 4.5 Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"800\" height=\"600\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--800x600.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV side view\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-side-view--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>It’s the same reason you’ll find no internal storage on the C68 Gravel. The team didn’t want to compromise on the bike’s silhouette or the tubes’ integrity. I admire the choice not to follow the trends and to keep the design focused on speed, handling, and beauty.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bb-non-drive--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV bb non drive\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bb-non-drive--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bb-non-drive--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bb-non-drive--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bb-non-drive--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bb-non-drive--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bb-non-drive--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bb-non-drive--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Now, the team says 42mm is the max, but that is the maximum for the rear tire. If you want to push the limits, you can get a larger tire in the front. But the fork is more sculpted than some, and you could run into mud clearance issues if you run bigger. The frame can fit gravel suspension forks if you’d like…but like the super wide tires and internal storage box — that might not be this kind of bike.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1675\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-full-bike--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-full-bike--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-full-bike--297x194.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-full-bike--800x523.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-full-bike--120x78.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-full-bike--768x502.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-full-bike--1536x1005.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-full-bike--2048x1340.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Colnago C68 Gravel Builds and Paint Options</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Currently, the C68 will come available as a frame and fork or in three different build options. The builds range from SRAM Red XPLR, Force XPLR, and Shimano GRX 822 mechanical.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-rider-view--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV bar rider view\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-rider-view--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-rider-view--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-rider-view--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-rider-view--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-rider-view--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-rider-view--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-bar-rider-view--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>The riders eye view of the Colnago CC.01 bar Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>All bikes will come equipped with Colnago CC.01 Wide integrated handlebar, Selle Italia Regal Short Open Fit CRB (Carbon) saddle, and Pirelli Cinturato Gravel TLR 40mm.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1693\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-black-paint--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV black paint\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-black-paint--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-black-paint--297x196.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-black-paint--800x529.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-black-paint--120x79.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-black-paint--768x508.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-black-paint--1536x1016.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-black-paint--2048x1355.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The wheels for each model change slightly, with the SRAM Red arriving with Zipp 303S carbon wheels, Force with Fulcrum Rapid Red 500, and the Shimano GRX with Fulcrum 900.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1920\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-joint--scaled.jpeg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Gravel JV seatpost joint\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-joint--scaled.jpeg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-joint--297x223.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-joint--800x600.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-joint--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-joint--768x576.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-joint--1536x1152.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Gravel-JV-seatpost-joint--2048x1536.jpeg 2048w\" /><figcaption>Bonded, lugged carbon with a seamless appearance Photos: Jordan Villella/Bikerumor)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Paint-wise, the new Colnago C68 Gravel will be available in Green Pearl (in most photos) or gloss black with red undertones in the sun. Having seen the paint up close, both are great options (I’m a glossy fan), but the Green Pearl should hide the scratches and abuse of gravel riding better. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-NFC--scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Grave NFC\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-NFC--scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-NFC--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-NFC--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-NFC--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-NFC--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-NFC--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-NFC--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-NFC--720x480.jpg 720w\" /><figcaption>(Photo: Colnago) </figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Colnago NFC Tag</h3>\n\n\n\n<p>Like other Colnago bikes, the new C68 will have a near-field communication or (<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/colnago-blockchain-security/\" target=\"_blank\">NFC</a>)<a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/colnago-blockchain-security/\" target=\"_blank\"> tag</a>. The tag is linked to the MyLime Polygon Blockchain and is inextricably linked to the bicycle. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em>How does this help the rider? </em>If your bike gets stolen, you can use the NFC as proof of ownership. The NFC also helps with re-sale and helps prevent (or disrupt) counterfeit Colnago bikes from entering the market. For more info, check out Colnago’s explanation of why they chose to be the first bicycle company to adopt<a href=\"https://www.colnago.com/stories/colnago-first-bicycle-manufacturer-to-adopt-blockchain\"> Blockchain here</a>.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><img width=\"2560\" height=\"1707\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--scaled.jpg\" alt=\"Colnago C68 Grave Full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--scaled.jpg 2560w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--297x198.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--800x533.jpg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--120x80.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--768x512.jpg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--1536x1024.jpg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--2048x1365.jpg 2048w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/01/Colnago-C68-Grave-Full-bike--720x480.jpg 720w\" /><figcaption>(Photo: Colnago)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Colnago C68 Gravel Pricing</h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Frameset only </strong>$7,100.00, €5,935, £5,269.00</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SRAM Red XPLR,</strong> ZIPP 303S Wheels, $13,199.95, €12,010.00, £11,099.99.99</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>SRAM Force XPLR,</strong> Fulcrum Rapid Red 500, $9,599.95, €8,690.00, £8,099.95</li>\n\n\n\n<li><strong>Shimano GRX 822 1X</strong>, Fulcrum Rapid Red 900, $7995.95, €7250.00, £6,899.95</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>Look for a ride review shortly, and for more information and availability near you, check out; <a href=\"https://www.colnago.com/bikes/gravel-bike/\">Colnago.com</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/colnago-made-in-italy-c68-gravel-race-bike/\">Colnago Unveils its Vision of Gravel Racing with the Italian Crafted C68 Gravel</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"b5552d976b7551f7605da43447cce9ed94347f73c2cc82b891bca35003c81bc7","category":"Cycling"}